<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-215-081 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 630 228</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Feb 28 1991 n1251 p35(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>BICC rides recession with PCs. (BICC Cables making good use oflocal area network)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>BICC Cables, one of the UK's biggest construction and wiringfirms, says its two-year-old local area network (LAN) ofmicrocomputers is helping it weather the recession.andP;  The EthernetLAN in Prescot, Merseyside, allows sales managers to access andmanage sales and order information on an ICL Superdual 2960mainframe computer in Penrith, Cumbria.andP;  The LAN consists of anApricot VX FT file server supporting about 50 Apricot Qicomputers.andP;  dBase IV databases with information about constructionprojects and BICC Cable's competition reside on the LAN.andP;  BICCCables is trying to promote the use of electronic data interchange(EDI) among its customers; so far, however, only one in 50 doesso.andP;  BICC Cables also runs a nationwide X.25 network.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   BICC Cables (Data processing).andO;Topic:     Local Area NetworksMicro-Mainframe CommunicationEnterprise-Wide NetworksCommunications ManagementSales ManagementConstruction IndustryNetwork ArchitectureCase Study.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>